				\begin{document}$$H$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M58"><mml:mi>H</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3775_Article_IEq26.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> contain the reconstructed haplotypes and the original haplotypes respectively. The RR describes the similarity between <inline-formula id="IEq27"><alternatives><tex-math id="M59">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hat{H}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M60"><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>H</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3775_Article_IEq27.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and <inline-formula id="IEq28"><alternatives><tex-math id="M61">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
